### 1. Step 1 – Place these files in your image

Create directories (if they don’t exist):

```bash
sudo mkdir -p /opt/scripts
```

#### File 1: First‑boot script (`/opt/scripts/first-boot.sh`)

```bash
#!/bin/bash
#
# Run once on first boot: regenerate IDs, set hostname, install K3s
#

set -euo pipefail

script_dir="/opt/scripts"
installed_flag="$script_dir/.first-boot-done"

# Only run once
if [ -f "$installed_flag" ]; then
    exit 0
fi

# 1) Regenerate machine ID
rm -f /etc/machine-id /var/lib/dbus/machine-id
systemd-machine-id-setup

# 2) Regenerate SSH host keys
rm -f /etc/ssh/ssh_host_*
dpkg-reconfigure openssh-server

# 3) Set hostname (optional)
new_hostname="k3s-single-node-$(date +%s)"
hostnamectl set-hostname "$new_hostname"

# 4) Configure K3s
# EDIT THESE FOR YOUR NETWORK:
STATIC_IP="192.168.1.100"
GATEWAY="192.168.1.1"
NAMESERVER="8.8.8.8"

K3S_EXEC="server \
  --no-deploy=traefik \
  --disable=local-storage \
  --node-external-ip=$STATIC_IP \
  --node-ip=$STATIC_IP"

# Install K3s
curl -sfL https://get.k3s.io | \
  K3S_KUBECONFIG_MODE="644" \
  INSTALL_K3S_EXEC="$K3S_EXEC" \
  sh -

# 5) Mark as done
touch "$installed_flag"

echo "First boot setup completed. K3s single‑node server ready."
echo "SSH: $STATIC_IP"
echo "kubeconfig: /etc/rancher/k3s/k3s.yaml"
```

Make it executable:

```bash
sudo chmod +x /opt/scripts/first-boot.sh
```

***

#### File 2: Systemd unit (`/etc/systemd/system/first-boot.service`)

```ini
[Unit]
Description=One‑time first‑boot setup for K3s single‑node static IP
After=network.target
ConditionPathExists=!/opt/scripts/.first-boot-done

[Service]
Type=oneshot
ExecStart=/bin/bash /opt/scripts/first-boot.sh
RemainAfterExit=yes

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target
```

Enable it so it runs on first boot:

```bash
sudo systemctl enable first-boot.service
```

