### 2. Step 2 – Configure static IP (netplan)

Edit `/etc/netplan/01-netcfg.yaml` (or similar) to match your network:

```yaml
network:
  version: 2
  renderer: networkd
  ethernets:
    eth0:
      dhcp4: false
      addresses:
        - 192.168.1.100/24
      gateway4: 192.168.1.1
      nameservers:
        addresses: [8.8.8.8, 1.1.1.1]
```

Run:

```bash
sudo netplan apply
```

You can change `192.168.1.100/24` and `192.168.1.1` to match your subnet.

